DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       pam_set_item  updates authentication information specified
       by item_type.  This function  takes  the  following  argu-
       ments: (In) The authentication handle returned by (In) The
       type of item. This may  be  one  of  the  following:  User
       authentication  token.   The  only  module  functions that
       should set this item are to pass an  authentication  token
       between modules in a stack, and to set the current authen-
       tication  token.   pam_conv  structure.    Previous   user
       authentication  token.   The  only  module  function  that
       should set this item is Remote  host  name.   Remote  user
       name.   Service name.  Terminal device name.  For physical
       devices, this is an absolute  pathname.   For  X  Windows-
       based  applications,  it is the value of the DISPLAY vari-
       able.  User name.  Default prompt for The default value is
       ``Please  enter  username:''.   (In) A pointer to the data
       object to be set or modified.  An item's data  is  changed
       if  it  had already been set within an authentication mod-
       ule.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       pam_set_item  returns  PAM_SUCCESS  if  successful   (this
       includes  the  case  where  a  requested item has not been
       set).  Otherwise, it returns one of  the  following  error
       codes: Buffer error.  System error.

